  "text": "The electronic structure found in the small particles is generally very discrete and not overlapping as is the case with the bulk material phases. This is due to the confinement of the electromagnetic wavefunctions to certain physical dimensions of the nanoparticles [CITATION_1] , an effect that is limited to the nanoscale [CITATION_2] .",
